    "description": "This seems to produce pleasing results no matter what aspect ratio we use. I used the following test script:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport yt\r\nfrom yt.units import kpc\r\nds = yt.load(\"IsolatedGalaxy/galaxy0030/galaxy0030\")\r\nfor wx in (5, 15, 20, 25, 40):\r\n    slc = yt.SlicePlot(ds, 'z', 'density', center=[0.5, 0.5, 0.5],\r\n                       width=(wx*kpc,20*kpc))\r\n    slc.annotate_scale(coeff=2.0, unit='kpc', pos=(0.1,0.1))\r\n    slc.save('%s' % wx)\r\n```",
